<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-11-23T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-11-23T12:00:00-05:00" n="393" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d393">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">500.C1199/247: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Consul at Geneva</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Gilbert</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-11-23T12:00:00-05:00">November
                                    23, 1936—noon</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>146. Department will probably wish to offer suggestion concerning
                            appointment of American to Economic Committee. Ascertain from Stoppani
                            latest date at which suggestion could be made.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Moore</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>